node.text: Introducing, “Hurricanes: Uncharted” – a new documentary series from New Jersey surfer/filmmaker duo @robkellysurf and @rsmallcheck, partnered up with Surfline’s forecast team, as they chase down swells on the East Coast in what’s shaping up to be an historic 2021 season. “There’s so much that goes on with these swells,” says Simalchick, “and the level of dedication that these people put into surfing is truly something worth capturing.” Hit the link in bio to read more about project.

🎥: @peterkingphoto

And he did so accordingly on National Tequila Day. | @josecuervotequila 
 
We want to say thanks to everyone that submitted entries! Public voting ends tonight at midnight. Who’s going to Surf Ranch? Vote now for your favorite entries through the link in bio.

Strapped with his arsenal of legos, a yoga mat tube simulator, and a hearty imagination, Max Montgomery (@tothemax2) depicts what the majority of us have experienced more times than we’d like to admit – a so-so surf session. But aside from his ingenious editing, what stood out most was Max’s passion for, as he said, “Helping those who often don’t get the chance to surf.”
 
Hit the link in bio to view all entries from the Surfline Spirit of Surfing Cuervo Challenge (@josecuervotequila) and vote for your favorite. Note: entry submission deadline ends on 11:59 p.m. PT Sunday, July 25th, so there’s still time to submit your video and secure your chance for a dream session at Surf Ranch with Gerry Lopez.

node.text: Introducing, “Hurricanes: Uncharted” – a new documentary series from New Jersey surfer/filmmaker duo @robkellysurf and @rsmallcheck, partnered up with Surfline’s forecast team, as they chase down swells on the East Coast in what’s shaping up to be an historic 2021 season. “There’s so much that goes on with these swells,” says Simalchick, “and the level of dedication that these people put into surfing is truly something worth capturing.” Hit the link in bio to read more about project.

node.text: By now, we’re all very familiar with @italoferreira in the water. But what about the man behind the knee-crunching aerials and the perennially stok-ed smile? A new documentary peels back the curtain on the world champ and gold medalist – from his humble beginnings in Baía Formosa, where he famously caught his first waves on a piece of styrofoam scrap, to his ascendence on the Championship Tour. And it’s playing now on Surfline. Hit the link in bio to watch “The Curious Tales of Italo Ferreira.”

node.text:
We just received our first Outer Banks report… well, one that didn’t come from our forecasters, at least. “Hurricane Larry swell has been hammering down on our coastline all day,” reports local shooter, Callaway Ramsey, “and the long-period swell has most of our sandbars shutting down. If you knew where to look, there were some gems to be had this morning. Finding this wave was the easy part. Trying to track down a close-enough friend to surf it with — that was the challenge.” Hit the link in bio for #ChasingHurricaneLarry realtime coverage.
📷: @callawayramsey

node.text:
This never happens in September, but it did. Two swells converged on southern Queensland this particular morning: one a classic tradewind swell from the east, the other a powerful south swell from the depths of the Tasman Sea off Sydney. They matched up against each other under a moderate offshore south-west wind, and the whole coast went round and slippery, including good ol’ Burleigh Heads. But where was everybody? “A couple were breaking up at Sharkies (way up the line),” says photographer Swilly. “Everyone was up there or in the Cove. But there was this other section, coming down into the mid-point area. You could have paddled out that morning, turned left, and had an absolute ball down there, all by yourself.” Happy days. And #GoodToEpic, for sure.
📷: @swillpics
